'''Wakakodama Kofun Cluster''' (若小玉古墳群, Wakakodama Kofun Cluster) is a group of {{ill|Kofun|en|Kofun|WD=Q1141225|lt=Kofun|1=Kofun}} (ancient Kofuns) located in {{ill|Gyōda|en|Gyōda|WD=Q860659|lt=Gyōda|1=Gyōda}}, {{ill|Saitama Prefecture|en|Saitama Prefecture|WD=Q128186|lt=Saitama Prefecture|1=Saitama Prefecture}}, Japan.

== Overview ==
As of the early {{ill|Shōwa period|ja|昭和時代|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shōwa period|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 昭和|1=Shōwa era|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q327567}}, the Wakakodama Kofun Cluster consisted of three keyhole-shaped tombs ({{ill|Zenpō-kōen-fun|en|Zenpō-kōen-fun|WD=Q11268718|lt=Zenpō-kōen-fun|1=Zenpō-kōen-fun}}), eight round tombs ({{ill|empun|ja|円墳|1=Round Kofun|1=Round Kofun|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/empun|13=User:Immanuelle/Round Kofun|comment=enwiki is a redirect}}), and several square tombs ({{ill|hōfun|ja|方墳|1=Square Kofun|1=Square Kofun|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/hōfun|13=User:Immanuelle/Square Kofun|comment=enwiki is a redirect}}), including prominent examples such as Atagoyama Kofun and Kojinyama Kofun. While most of the kofun have been leveled to make way for the {{ill|Fujimi Industrial Complex|ja|富士見工業団地|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fujimi Industrial Complex|qq=}}, {{ill|Hachimanyama Kofun (Gyoda)|lt=Hachimanyama Kofun (Gyoda)|lt=Hachiman-yama Kofun (Gyoda)|ja|八幡山古墳 (行田市)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hachiman-yama Kofun (Gyoda)|qq=}} and {{ill|Jizōzuka Kofun (Gyōda)|lt=Jizōzuka Kofun (Gyōda)|lt=Jizōzuka Kofun (Gyoda)|ja|地蔵塚古墳 (行田市)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jizōzuka Kofun (Gyoda)|qq=}} remain intact.

The kofun in this cluster are characterized by their dense distribution atop the region's narrow loam plateau, where they coexisted with evidence of residential sites. Notably, the Sanpōzuka Kofun was built directly over a residential site.

The construction of the Wakakodama Kofun Cluster is believed to have taken place after the cessation of tomb construction in the {{ill|Sakitama Kofun Cluster|en|Sakitama Kofun Cluster|WD=Q2213580|lt=Sakitama Kofun Cluster|1=Sakitama Kofun Cluster}}, likely reflecting the rise of a new local ruling family.<ref name=Tashiro>{{Cite book|last=Tashiro|title=Saitama no Rekishi|publisher=Yamakawa Shu11ansha|year=2010|pages=46–47}}</ref>

== List of Kofun ==
* {{ill|Hachimanyama Kofun (Gyoda)|lt=Hachimanyama Kofun (Gyoda)|lt=Hachiman-yama Kofun (Gyoda)|ja|八幡山古墳 (行田市)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hachiman-yama Kofun (Gyoda)|qq=}} - Round tomb (Prefectural Historic Site); also referred to as "The Stone Stage of the Kanto."<ref>{{Cite web|author=Gyoda City Board of Education, Cultural Property Protection Division|url=https://www.city.gyoda.lg.jp/41/03/10/bunkazai_itiran/hatimanyamakofunsekisitu.html|title=Hachiman-yama Kofun Stone Chamber|work=Gyoda City|date=2015-11-02|accessdate=2020-07-16}}</ref>
* {{ill|Jizōzuka Kofun (Gyōda)|lt=Jizōzuka Kofun (Gyōda)|lt=Jizōzuka Kofun (Gyoda)|ja|地蔵塚古墳 (行田市)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jizōzuka Kofun (Gyoda)|qq=}} - Square tomb (Prefectural Historic Site)
* Atagoyama Kofun - Keyhole-shaped tomb
* Kojinyama Kofun - Keyhole-shaped tomb
: Total length: 74 meters; construction era: early 6th century
* Sasazuka Kofun - Round tomb
* Sanpōzuka Kofun - Keyhole-shaped tomb
: Total length: approximately 70 meters; features a tategata moats and external protrusions.<ref>{{Cite book|author=Wada Harugo|title=Zenpō-kōen-fun Shūsei: Tohoku and Kanto Vol.|publisher=Yamakawa Shu11ansha|year=1994|page=616}}</ref>
* Kusen-zuka Kofun - Round tomb
* Yoroizuka Kofun - Round tomb
Three additional unnamed tombs are present in the area.

